##DESCRIPTION
##  Find the derivatives of a fraction of two
##  polynomial evaluated at a point, use that to
##  find the equation of the tangent line of the curve at that point
##ENDDESCRIPTION

##Tagged by ynw2d

## DBsubject(Calculus - single variable)
## DBchapter(Differentiation)
## DBsection(Quotient rule (without trigonometric functions))
## Institution(ASU)
## MLT(quotRulenoTrigMiscTangent)
## Level(2)
## TitleText1('Calculus: Early Transcendentals')
## AuthorText1('Rogawski')
## EditionText1('1')
## Section1('3.2')
## Problem1('12')
## TitleText2('Calculus: Early Transcendentals')
## AuthorText2('Stewart')
## EditionText2('6')
## Section2('2.7')
## Problem2('12')
## KEYWORDS('Derivatives', 'tangent line')


DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(2,5,1);
$b1 = random(2,3,1);
$c1 = random(2,7,1);
$d1 = random(2,6,1);
$n1 = random(3,7,1);
$x1 = random(4,5,1);
$y1 = ($a1*$x1)/(1+$x1**2);
$m1 = $a1*(1-$x1**2)/(1+$x1**2)**2;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
If 
\[ f(x) = \frac {$a1 x }{1+ x^2} \]
find \( f'( $x1 ) \).
$BR $BR \{ans_rule(30) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = $m1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Use this to find the equation of the tangent line to the curve
 \( y =    \frac {$a1 x }{1+ x^2}  \)
at the point \( ( $x1 , !{$y1:%.5f} ) \).
The equation of this tangent line can be written in the form \( y = mx+b \)
where \( m \) is: \{ans_rule(30) \}
$BR
EOT
$ans = $m1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and  where \( b \) is: \{ans_rule(30) \}
$BR
EOT
$ans = $y1 -$m1*$x1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
